                <a href="~/home/support" id="menu_support" title="Support">
                    Support
                </a>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="page-header">
        <h1>NetInventory</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="page-content">
        <div class="single-body">
            <h2>What is NetInventory?</h2>
            <div class="sub-content">
                <div class="sub-content-head">
                    <h3>Network Inventory and Asset Management</h3>
                </div>
                <p>
                    NetInventory is an SQL database used to track all IT assets.
                </p>
                <p>Including:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Servers</li>
                    <li>Network Appliances</li>
                    <li>Workstations</li>
                    <li>Phones</li>
                    <li>Projectors</li>
                    <li>Printers</li>
                    <li>And more.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="sub-content">
                <div class="sub-content-head">
                    <h3>Network Documentation</h3>
                </div>
                <p>
                    NetInventory provides quick access to standardized documentation about
                    computers, servers, network appliances, printers, and all other IT assests.
                </p>
                <p>Including:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Server and workstation specs</li>
                    <li>Switch port maps</li>
                    <li>IP address tracking</li>
                    <li>Device locations</li>
                    <li>And more.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="sub-content">
                <div class="sub-content-head">
                    <h3>Living</h3>
                </div>
                <p>
                    NetInventory is a living system. It should be updated
                    every time a new entity is added.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
        <img src="~/images/logo.png" width="180px"/><br />
        Design by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ericclaus/">Eric Claus</a>
    </div>
</body>